ound"></path></svg></button></button></div></div></div><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 buSEYI"><div id="app-0" data-section-title="KEY_TAKEAWAYS_OVERVIEW" class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 kImjEf"><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 kImjEf"><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 hdcXFt"><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 SummaryParagraph__DirectionalContainer-sc-3d035568-0 jHXxZe cRFZlx"><div class="FreeStyleSummaryMarkdown-styled__Markdown-sc-de9c7c46-0 bBUTNJ prose prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-pre:p-0 free-style-summary-section"><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Meeting Schedule Revamped:</strong> Meetings to be held Fridays at 11 AM and Mondays at 3 PM starting February 23rd.</p></span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Testing of Game Features:</strong> Focused on hands-on testing, identified bugs in trading and production features. Paul to maintain a bug list on GitHub.</p></span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>UI Terms Causing Confusion:</strong> Negotiation terms like “buy requests” need clarity; suggested renaming for better understanding of roles.</p></span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>CSV Export Issues:</strong> Reports showed incomplete data or only headers; multiple bugs in downloads acknowledged for further investigation.</p></span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Progress and Future Focus:</strong> Team optimistic about project despite ongoing UI and feature issues; encouraged continued gameplay and bug reporting.</p></span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Negotiation Process Simplified:</strong> Agreed to streamline buy/sell steps by removing unnecessary inputs, enhancing user clarity in gameplay.</p></span></span></div></li>
</ul></div></div></div></div></div><div id="app-1" data-section-title="Summary" class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 kImjEf"><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 efjueN"><strong class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 iObbO"><span color="secondary" class="Text-styled__Root-sc-fca7f555-0 iEedXv">Notes</span></strong></div><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 kImjEf"><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 hdcXFt"><div class="Box-styled__Box-sc-6ede6fd4-0 SummaryParagraph__DirectionalContainer-sc-3d035568-0 jHXxZe cRFZlx"><div class="FreeStyleSummaryMarkdown-styled__Markdown-sc-de9c7c46-0 bBUTNJ prose prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-pre:p-0 free-style-summary-section"><h2><strong>Scheduling and Coordination</strong></h2>
<p>The team agreed to reschedule their upcoming meetings to accommodate everyone's availability around President’s Day and other commitments (<a rel="nofollow">04:01</a>).</p>
<ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Friday 11 AM Meeting Set</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">07:15</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Chose Friday at 11 AM as the preferred meeting time to avoid conflicts with faculty meetings.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Aracely agreed to adjust her schedule to accommodate this timing.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert and Tom planned to meet separately before Friday to review the project.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">The group acknowledged the need for flexibility with potential changes due to faculty scheduling.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Monday Recurring Meeting Confirmed</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">11:58</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Agreed to hold recurring meetings on Mondays at 3 PM starting the 23rd.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul and Aracely confirmed availability; Tom and Herbert also agreed.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Aracely set up co-host access in Zoom for upcoming meetings to ensure continued access during her absence.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Aracely mentioned a planned three-week absence and promised to update the team on dates.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Game Testing and Feedback Process</strong></h2>
<p>The team focused on hands-on testing of the game’s trading and production features, identifying bugs, and clarifying user experience (<a rel="nofollow">10:37</a>).</p>
<ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Initial Playthrough and Bug Discovery</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">18:14</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul demonstrated game mechanics, including production revenue calculation based on chemical trades.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">The team explored the logic behind shadow prices, slack, and inventory changes during trades.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert and Tom began testing the buy/sell negotiation interface, identifying confusing terminology and UI inconsistencies.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul committed to maintaining a bug and feature list on a Kanban board hosted on GitHub for streamlined issue tracking.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>GitHub and Project Management Setup</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">13:09</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul introduced a Kanban board concept for tracking bugs and development tasks, requiring GitHub accounts for access.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Aracely and others discussed their GitHub accounts; Paul planned to add contributors for collaborative issue management.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">They noted the need for manual refreshes on the board to see updates in real time.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">The team agreed this tool would help organize ongoing development and bug fixes.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Game Interface and User Experience Issues</strong></h2>
<p>The team identified several UI and functional issues impacting clarity and usability during game play and negotiation (<a rel="nofollow">38:50</a>).</p>
<ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Confusing Terminology in Negotiations</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">39:44</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Terms like “buy request” and “negotiation with seller” caused confusion about transaction roles.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert and Paul discussed that “buy requests” act more like transaction announcements rather than clear buy/sell offers.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">They suggested renaming columns and clarifying language to explicitly state who is buyer and who is seller.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Acceptance, rejection, and counteroffer buttons were sometimes unclear in their effect.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Inconsistent Screen Behavior and Transaction Flow</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">50:27</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert struggled with switching between admin and player views, as the interface lacks a direct toggle.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">They confirmed the need to “hard reset” before starting new games to clear NPC teams and data.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">The team observed some UI elements jumping or refreshing unexpectedly, possibly related to Zoom or browser issues.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul noted the sound effects and notifications were inconsistent or missing during negotiation actions.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Linear Programming Calculations and Data Accuracy</strong></h2>
<p>The team analyzed the correctness and update logic of production revenue, shadow prices, and transaction results, seeking consistency and clarity (<a rel="nofollow">48:14</a>).</p>
<ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Validation of Production Revenue and Net Profit Calculations</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">49:52</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert verified that production revenue, sales revenue, and purchase costs align mathematically to net profit after trades.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">They noted production revenue should not change when selling excess chemicals unused in production.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul confirmed the calculations are correct but some displayed delta values were misplaced or misleading.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">The team agreed the data presentation needs to better differentiate changes due to production versus sales.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Shadow Price Recalculation and UI Update Timing</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">54:55</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Tom emphasized that after each transaction, the linear program (LP) should be rerun to update production values and shadow prices.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul suggested marking values as stale or unknown (e.g., replacing with question marks) until recalculation occurs.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert and Tom debated pros and cons of automatic recalculation versus requiring manual user action for learning purposes.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Consensus leaned toward automatic LP recalculation after transactions with clear UI cues prompting users to review updated shadow prices.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Reporting and Export Functionality</strong></h2>
<p>The team tested CSV export features for game reports, identifying bugs and incomplete data issues (<a rel="nofollow">36:30</a>).</p>
<ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><strong>Problems with CSV Downloads</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">37:02</a>)</span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Downloads like the leaderboard CSV contained only headers without data, indicating export bugs.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Other report types like market history showed partial data but revealed inconsistencies and missing fields.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul acknowledged multiple bugs remain in report exports and planned to investigate further.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert committed to reviewing downloaded reports in detail and providing feedback to improve accuracy and completeness.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<h2><strong>Next Steps and Team Outlook</strong></h2>
<p>The team expressed optimism about the project progress despite outstanding issues, planning further testing and iterative improvements (<a rel="nofollow">41:41</a>).</p>
<ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Ongoing Play and Bug Reporting</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">41:58</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul encouraged the team to continue playing the game during the week and report bugs.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Herbert planned to analyze reports to ensure they meet information needs.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Tom and Herbert noted that the core logic and calculations are sound; remaining issues are mostly UI and layout related.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">The team sees the project as promising and is motivated to refine the experience.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class=""><p><strong>Discussion on Negotiation Process Simplification</strong> (<a rel="nofollow">43:02</a>)</p></span></span></div><ul node="[object Object]">
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">The group agreed to simplify buy/sell negotiation steps by removing unnecessary inputs like price or quantity at buy request creation.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Instead, buy requests will simply indicate interest, allowing negotiation of amount and price during offers.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">This mimics the classroom process and reduces confusion in the interface.</span></span></div></li>
<li class="expandable-list-item"><div class="header-container"><span><span class="">Paul and the team will keep this in mind during upcoming play sessions and development adjustments.</span></span></div></li>
</ul></li>
